   spatio-temporal cases on the two types of spatial domains are reported.
   We describe the results of testing the stationarity of Pacific wind
   data, and of testing the axial symmetry of climate model errors for
   surface temperature using the NOAA GFDL model outputs and the
   observations from the Climate Research Unit in East Anglia and the
