Abstract = {{Geostatistical simulations often require the generation of numerous
   realizations of a stationary Gaussian process over a regularly meshed
   sample grid Omega. This paper shows that for many important correlation
   functions in geostatistics, realizations of the associated process over
   m + 1 equispaced points on a line can be produced at the cost of an
   initial FFT of length 2m with each new realization requiring an
   additional FFT of the same length. In particular, the paper first notes
   that if an (m + 1) x (m + 1) Toeplitz correlation matrix R can be
   embedded in a nonnegative definite 2M x 2M circulant matrix S, exact
   realizations of the normal multivariate y similar to N(O, R) can be
   generated via FFTs of length 2M. Theoretical results are then presented
   to demonstrate that for many commonly used correlation structures the
   minimal embedding in which M = m is nonnegative definite. Extensions to
   simulations of stationary fields in higher dimensions are also provided
